metadata.name: Missplaced #100
metadata.description:
Being in a space, knowing that we are enveloped by an object—a ground or a wall—made us aware of our external reality. And when a space gains social, cultural, or emotional meaning, it becomes a place.

But sometimes, these spaces and places betray us, isolating the inhabitants who live in them, as if every room and ground are turning hostile and apathetic to the beings who live within its own walls.

In the end, as a way to confirm our being, we are wired to belong to a place, whether it's a theoretical place or a physical place. This feeling of being misplaced can happen even in the most hospitable places in the universe.

------------

4 Variant of "Home"
4 Variant of "Environment"
and some Planetary

metadata.description:
Containment has been breached and Missingno is on the loose. 
This unique beast doesn’t have a fixed shape and its appearance is ever-changing.

metadata.name: Tesseract #175
metadata.description:
'Tesseract' is a generative collection drawing on the concept of the cube from oneirology, the interpretation of dreams. In many mythologies and fields of study, the square is considered a 'perfect shape', thus with its abstraction into three isometric dimensions, the cube is seen by some as a representation of the various aspects of the human condition.

In 'Tesseract', the ribbons flowing between the cubes represent the shared experiences that connect us all. No matter how different our lives might be, we all go through the same joys, sorrows, trials, tribulations and experience attachments of varying degrees. 

It is these experiences that bind us together and make us who we are. With these concepts in mind, viewers are invited to interpret each composition as it relates to them and their unique story, from the perspective of that which has been and that which is yet to be experienced.

Press 'S' to save a high resolution PNG at 2400 x 3396 px.

metadata.name: In Due Time #78
metadata.description:
“In Due Time” is a collaborative generative collection between artists Melissa Wiederrecht and Amber Vittoria. Inspired by Wiederrecht’s mastery of line and Vittoria’s notable palette, this 1/1/250 series captures the present moment. It serves as a reminder that we are more similar than we are different, leveraging homogeneous shapes to create distinctive compositions.

Vittoria’s poem for the collection:

“In Due Time”
We will all become
Particles dancing
Across the skyline.

The artwork listed is indeed authentic, created by, and copyright to artists Melissa Wiederrecht and Amber Vittoria; the purchase of this NFT is a purchase of the asset, not of the copyright.

-------------------------------------------

To save a high-resolution image for printing, click “open” under the image on the page for your token, and then hit:

Digits “1” through “9” to get an image that is 1000 through 9000px tall.  This may take a while, depending on the size and your computer, so please be patient.

metadata.name: Trading Art #69
metadata.description:
Visualize the price chart of major Forex pairs, BTC and ETH.

There are 5000 H1 candle data imported for each one, which means more than 50K H1 candles in total, with random background color, background patterns, and moving average period and style it provides good enough variations.

I start coding from first Covid quarantine by the Forex trading bots, first MQL4 then Python, and so on, in all of those experiences I have to play all the time with the OHLC data, which stands for Open, High, Low, and close price of a specific period, for example, one hour(H1).

Now I use them to make generative color paint for those people who are interested in Forex or Trading and spend a lot of time seeing these candles on the screen!

You can hold it in your wallet or print it and hang it on the wall.

Press “s” key to save in original size.

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: rememberance #62
metadata.description:
A field of slit-scan flowers, created from slicing images from my "abstracted expressions" acrylic painting/collage series, minted on exchange.art ( https://exchange.art/series/abstracted%20expression/nfts ). I have been looking for a way to bridge my code-based art on Tezos with my physical art on Solana, and this is an attempt to do so. 

The 9 paintings used in the piece are all acrylic, charcoal, wax pastel, and collage on paper, scanned at 600dpi. The FxHash mint is coded in p5.js

metadata.name: A Less Traveled Path #190
metadata.description:
"I shall be telling this with a sigh
Somewhere ages and ages hence:
Two roads diverged in a wood, and I—
I took the one less traveled by,
And that has made all the difference."

- Robert Frost, The Road Not Taken



=========

Controls:
[1] set resolution to 1024x1024 (default)
[2] set resolution to 2048x2048 
[3] set resolution to 4096x4096
[0] set resolution to window size (might help on lower end computers)

[c] capture a screenshot at rendered resolution


Made with cables.gl, a node-based webgl environment
XALTED 2022
